-- Germany Had Warm, Sunny August With Below-Average Rain
-- B y   R u d y   R u i t e n b e r g
-- 2012-09-10T15:53:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-10/germany-had-warm-sunny-august-with-below-average-rain.html
Germany  had a warm and sunny
August, with less rainfall than usual, meteorological office
Deutscher Wetterdienst reported.  The average temperature for Germany of 18.4 degrees Celsius
(65.1 degrees Fahrenheit) was 1 degree above normal for the
1981-2010 period, making last month the 12th-warmest August
since 1891, the office wrote in a  report  on its website today.  Rainfall was an average 64.7 millimeters (2.55 inches), 17
percent less than normal in the 30-year period through 2010,
Deutscher Wetterdienst wrote. The country had 234.9 hours of
sunshine, about 30 hours more than usual, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Rudy Ruitenberg in Paris at 
